post_text:
Bus Seat Assignments Update: Bus seat assignments are now available in the Ride360. Once in the App, click the + sign for your seat assignment.

Your child’s seat assignment is for whatever ride you indicated that they need on the parent survey in early August.

If you indicated they needed a ride for AM only, PM only or both AM and PM the seat assignment is the same for all rides.

Please note the seating is numbered and lettered starting from row 1 on the passenger side of the bus:

Seat A is window seat door side
Seat B is middle seat door side
Seat C is aisle seat door side
Seat D is aisle seat driver side
Seat E is middle seat driver side
Seat F is window seat driver side

Most seat assignments will be seats A and F. The only instances where other letters are use are where siblings from the same house are sitting together.

Click here for information from the Transportation webpage on the District website at: https://www.westgenesee.org/district-services/transportation/

School Supply Drive Distribution is Tomorrow, August 29

The West Genesee PTA/PTO District Council has partnered with Staples on Milton Ave again this year for the School Supply Drive. This year it will be especially important for kids to have their own school supplies. A big thank you to the community for your contributions and commitment to our students!

Pick-up of supplies will occur tomorrow, August 29. Details about where and when were emailed directly to parents that registered to receive the supplies. If you have questions about the program or pick-up, please contact them at westgennydistrictcouncil@gmail.com.

The West Genesee District Council is committed to ensuring that students have the supplies they need to be successful in school. If you have a student that needs school supplies, please email the District Council for assistance at the email address listed above. All requests are confidential.

*Statewide, lower-risk sports (e.g. tennis & soccer) may practice & play beginning 9/21.
*No travel games or practice permitted outside school's region or neighboring regions until 10/19.
*Full-contact sports can practice but aren't authorized to compete.

Amended West Genesee CSD District Calendar for 2020-2021 Approved at BOE Meeting

At the Board of Education Meeting held on August 12, 2020, an amended calendar moving the start date of school for WGCSD students to September 10 was approved.

Other adjustments to the calendar include:
-Superintendent Conference Day on March 15, 2021 moved to September 8, 2020
-Superintendent Workshop Half-Day on November 3 and Half-Day on May 20 moved to September 9, 2020 (full day)

The AMENDED 2020-2021 calendar is now available on the website by clicking here: https://www.westgenesee.org/about-us/calendars/

IMPORTANT REMINDER About Selection of Options for Students through Schooltool

In the West Genesee reopening plan, parents have the option of selecting in-person/hybrid learning or remote learning.

An additional critical piece of information we need is whether or not you may be able to transport your child(ren).

Please follow this link and login to Schooltool (https://wg.schooltool.cnyric.org/schooltoolweb/) to let us know your decisions for each of your children. (Further instructions on submitting the survey is available via video at the top of the Schooltool homepage.)

Please send these commitments back no later than August 10, 2020.

Also, if you do not remember your Schooltool ID and/or Password, please click on "New User or Forgot Password" link" in Schooltool. You can also contact the Central Registrar at centralregistrar@westgenesee.org or (315) 487-4683 for assistance with Schooltool. Just a reminder... when using a mobile device to please select “view full site” as shown in the image with this article.

https://www.westgenesee.org/letter_reopening_options/

School-Specific Talks with the Superintendent on School Reopening

The West Genesee PTAs and PTOs are pleased to host Superintendent of Schools, David C. Bills, for building-specific Talks with the Superintendent. These talks will address parent questions and concerns on the reopening of schools in the fall.

Each PTA/PTO will email parents/guardians of their school an invitation to participate in the discussion for their schools. (They will come separately per school PTA/PTO.) If you have a student in multiple schools feel free to register in the schools of each of your children.

CMS PTO - Mon., 7/27, 6 pm
WGHS PTSA - Tue., 7/28, 6 pm
WGMS PTA - Wed., 7/29 6 pm
ST PTA - Mon., 8/3, 6 pm
SR PTO - Tue., 8/4, 6 pm
EH PTA - Wed., 8/5, 6 pm
OR PTA - Mon., 8/10, 6 pm
*Invitations will be sent directly to parents from the respective PTA/PTO at least one week prior to the scheduled date.

post_text:
WGHS Juniors Invited to Boys and Girls State

Two West Genesee High School juniors were invited to attend the American Legion Boys State sponsored by the Camillus Post #1540.

The boys who were selected to attend are: Andrew Sheedy and Keegan Scharoun.

Two girls from West Genesee High School were selected for Girls State as delegates and three girls as alternates. Danesia Patterson and Mia Coots were chosen to be delegates and Velika Zaitseva, Sarah Petrus, and Julia Colabufo were alternates.

These events involve a week of educational programs that teach government from the township to the state level. These selected students exhibited the most outstanding qualities of leadership, character, scholarship, loyalty, and service to their school.

These are annually scheduled to occur at the end of June. Unfortunately, both summer programs were cancelled due to COVID-19.

Congratulations!!!

https://www.westgenesee.org/wghs-juniors-invited-to-boys-and-girls-state/

post_text:
Wildcats Celebrate Today’s Heroes

The West Genesee Class of 2020 is paying an admirable tribute to the first responders who have been at the heart of treating patients with COVID-19. This will take shape in a message that will begin appearing on the electronic billboard at Township 5 beginning today, Thursday, June 18 through June 24.

The images are of graduates in caps and gowns, and medical personal in full PPE. The message to all these medical heroes?

“WE CAN WEAR OUR CAPS AND GOWNS,
BECAUSE YOU WORE YOURS.
THANK YOU
FROM THE CLASS OF 2020
WEST GENESEE”

This tribute image and message was created by artist, Julia Winfield, a 1983 graduate of West Genesee High School. Julia has an art and design business in Charlotte, NC, and has donated this piece to her alma mater, where she believes students are encouraged to value the accomplishments of others.

https://www.westgenesee.org/wildcats-celebrate-todays-heroes/

WGHS National Art Honor Society Video Celebration

This year we were proud to establish the West Genesee High School chapter of the National Art Honor Society (NAHS).

The goal of NAHS is to not only recognize students for their artistic ability, but to also empower students to become leaders in our school and local community through arts-based service and professional artistic development.

Our inaugural group of 45 members are led by our officers:

Hailey Kremenek, President
Fateema Islam, Vice President
Maison Lamanna, Secretary
Gabriela Corso, Treasurer
Riley Kiteveles, Event Coordinator

While we could not have our in-person exhibition and ceremony, we are excited to share and celebrate these students through this video posted at the top of this webpage or directly by clicking here: https://ensemble.cnyric.org/Watch/Qc42Hty8. We hope you enjoy!

Annual Meeting and Election of Board of Education Candidates Update

Pursuant to Executive Order 202.39, dated June 8, 2020, the date of the Annual Meeting and Election of Board of Education Candidates has been changed from June 9, 2020 to June 16, 2020.

Specific details are follows:

Ballots may be dropped off in person at the District Office, 300 Sanderson Drive, Camillus, NY, 13031 until 5:00 p.m., June 9, 2020 (today). At this time the ballot box will be removed and no additional in-person ballot drop off is allowed, per executive order 202.39.

Ballots returned by mail will continue to be accepted through 5:00 p.m., June 16, 2020, per executive order 202.39.

At 5:00 p.m. on June 16, 2020, all hand delivered ballots received by June 9, 2020 and all mailed ballots received by June 16, 2020, will be canvased and tallied, per executive order 202.39.

https://www.westgenesee.org/annual-meeting-and-election-of-board-of-education-candidates-change/

PLEASE NOTE: There has been an adjustment to the second bullet in the Distribution of Diplomas section of the graduation communication. Each graduate will be allowed to arrive with TWO cars of immediate family members on June 20, 2020.

Getting real-world experience

During the first weeks of the OCM BOCES shift to off-campus learning earlier this year, West Genesee Central School District construction student Parker Martinez joined professional contractors on a project to build a new Dunkin' near the Regional Market. His teacher, Mike Cavender, had suggested authentic learning opportunities, so Martinez stepped up to the challenge while he could. In the photo, Martinez works near a highway overpass and billboard near the Regional Market. Great job Parker!

#OCMBOCES #BOCESConnects

West Genesee Student Wins at New York-New England Optimist District Oratorical Competition

The New York-New England District Optimist Oratorical Competition was held on May 23, 2020 remotely through Zoom. The winner was West Genesee High School senior Christina Van Allen representing the Camillus Optimist Club. She will move forward to the World Competition being held online on July 16-17.

The third place winner was West Genesee High School senior Hannah Craybas who was also representing the Camillus Optimist Club.

Congratulations!

Click here to read the full article.

The West Genesee Central School District's 2020-2021 Budget vote will take place via Absentee Ballots this year. The Absentee Ballots were mailed to voters in the District yesterday.

If you do not receive a ballot by June 2, 2020, and you are an eligible voter, please email Paul E. Pelton, District Clerk at 2020budgetvote@westgenesee.org.

The ballots are due by 5 p.m. on Tuesday, June 9, at the West Genesee Central School District Office. You will receive a pre-addressed postage paid envelope to return your ballot.

Details about the 2020-2021 budget, biographies of board candidates, and more are available in our budget newsletter, which you should have received in the mail by the end of today. You can view a PDF of the Communicator Budget Edition Newsletter at https://www.westgenesee.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/wgBudget-Issue-2020_FINAL_colorforweb.pdf

This year’s Budget Vote/BOE Election will be held on Tuesday, June 9, and all voting will be done through absentee ballots. An absentee ballot, to be returned via a postage pre-paid return envelope, will be mailed to voters on or about May 26, 2020.

The Public Budget Hearing will be on Wednesday, May 27, at 7:00 p.m. via video livestream at
https://ensemble.cnyric.org/hapi/v1/contents/permalinks/f8D4Qyt3/view

For more information about the budget and information stated above, click here:
https://www.westgenesee.org/about-us/budget-information/

post_text:
This time has been so difficult and art teacher Gigina Long was inspired by her students' resilience and their creative drive. Their assignment? Create art. Experience the joy & peace that art can provide. No "traditional" supplies? Look around you-everything can become art in the hands of an artist!

Some students tackled recreating famous artworks. 💙 how they took their own spin on the challenge. We've got LEGO from Logan B., chalk art from Maribeth T., Starry Night created in Minecraft from Mackenzie B., and a DBZ parody of American Gothic by Makayla L.

This time at home has also unlocked a new opportunity for students to explore - the kitchen! Some students have been exploring no-waste food art. A landscape created w/ homemade focaccia & veggies! Underwater seascape! Delicious & beautiful! Bread by Ava P. & Seascape by Anna I.

Food Distribution Information/Update

With the announcement of schools not returning to regular schedules this year, we are putting in place the food distribution schedule for the remainder of May, 2020 through June, 2020. Please see below for more detailed information.

May 11, 2020 - Five days of meals (covers 5/12, 5/13, 5/14, 5/15, 5/18)

May 18, 2020 - Six days of meals (covers 5/19, 5/20, 5/21, 5/22, 5/25, 5/26)

May 26, 2020 - Four days of meals (covers 5/27, 5/28, 5/29, 6/1)

June 1, 2020 - Five days of meals (covers 6/2, 6/3, 6/4, 6/5, 6/8)

June 8, 2020 - Five days of meals (covers 6/9, 6/10, 6/11, 6/12, 6/15)

June 15, 2020 - Five days of meals (covers 6/16, 6/17, 6/18, 6/19, 6/22)

June 22, 2020 - Five days of meals (covers 6/23, 6/24, 6/25, 6/26, 6/29)

June 29, 2020 - To Be Determined

As more information is released from New York State, we will notify you of any changes to the above schedule.

https://www.westgenesee.org/food-distribution-info-and-updates/

post_text:
Get Ready for the PTA/PTO Virtual Spirit Week Two-April 20-24!

Celebrate our community and show your West Genesee Pride!

Email pictures of your students during virtual spirit week to your school PTA/PTO to be shared on Facebook/Twitter.

Follow your PTA/PTO's on social media to share in the fun.

Below are the daily themes:

Movie Monday: Send us a picture of you watching your favorite movie! Or dress up as a character from your favorite movie

Travel Tuesday: If you could go anywhere where would you go?! Draw a picture and show us where you’d go. Anywhere in the world!

Warm-Up Wednesday: Send us a video of your favorite Dance moves!

Thoughtful Thursday: Share something nice you did for someone in your house today!

Fresh Air Friday: Weather permitting, get outside and show us what fun things you find! Enjoy the fresh air!!

West Genesee is Again One of the Best Music Communities for Music Education!

The National Association of Music Merchants (NAMM) Foundation has announced the results of its 21st annual “Best Communities for Music Education” (BCME) survey, which acknowledges schools and districts across the U.S. for their commitment and support of music education in schools.

This is the twelfth consecutive year, fifteenth time overall, that West Genesee has been recognized for this honor. Congratulations! 🎶🎵💙🎉💛🎵🎶 #wildcatpride

post_text:
Update from Supt Bills on April 6, 2020: Remain Closed through April 29, 2020

This afternoon, at the daily press conference, NYS Governor Andrew Cuomo announced the continuation and extension of “pause” (previous Executive Order) until April 29, 2020.

In order to further promote the need for social distancing, school property (including playgrounds) will remain closed through April 29, 2020. We look forward to opening these facilities when the environment is safer at a later date.

Also today, at the NYS Board of Regents meeting, Chancellor Rosa announced that the June Regents exams are cancelled. Additional guidance on this matter will be released soon. Updates will be forwarded at that time.

To read the rest of the message, click here:
https://www.westgenesee.org/update-from-supt-bills-on-april-6-2020/

Childcare Survey
If you are a parent or caregiver who needs child care, please complete this parent need for child care survey at https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/3HSNNYJ.

Based on the information you provide about your job, employer, number of children, and financial need, the Office of Children and Family Services (OCFS) may be able to help you find the child program you need. It may be a challenge to find child care due to COVID-19 related program closures, however the staff at OCFS are trying their best to support families to find the high quality child care that they need.

Food Donations Information
We would like to thank all of you for your generous donations to date. The most common question is, “What items are you in need of most?” Currently our plan is to utilize most pantry items to provide food for what would have been our April Break Week (April 4-12).

With this in mind, we believe simple, non-perishable meal items would serve the community the best. Ideas are as follows:

Man n Cheese
Pasta and Sauce
Canned Soup
Tuna Fish
Peanut Butter and Jelly
Bread
Boxes of Cereal
Beverages
Granola
Snacks
Etc.

Thank you for your continued support of our community during this challenging time.

Donations can be dropped off at the main entrance between the hours of 9:00 a.m. to Noon, Monday-Friday, at West Genesee High School, 5201 West Genesee Street, Camillus, New York 13031.

https://www.westgenesee.org/food-donations-information/

post_text: Check out this awesome project that WGHS Technology Teacher Matt Makowiec has been working on to help out during the Coronavirus COVID-19 pandemic. #WildcatPride
shared_text:
Matt Makowiec is at West Genesee Central School District.
March 21 at 12:31 AM · Camillus, NY ·

First off hope everyone is doing well! With help from our Instructional Technology Department and the go ahead from my administration at West Genesee Central School District, I have brought our Makerbot #Z18 #3DPrinters out of quarantine and set up a mini print farm to help Budmen Industries, a local company, 3D print #COVID19 face shields! I am proud to work for a district that understands how important this issue is and am proud to report I'm up to 8 #3DFaceShield parts and now printing 6 at a time. A big thanks also to my wife Daniella and puppy Charlotte for putting up with all of the strange Star Wars type noises coming from the basement haha. #flatteningthecurve And not to be blunt but if you think this is no big deal, that it won't happen to you and are walking around like nothing going to happen to you please remember there are many that you love that ARE at risk and ARE in harm's way so STAY HOME! https://budmen.com/

Follow me or Budmen Industries on Twitter @MrMakWGHS @budmenind for more daily progress posts!

Technology Distribution Begins March 18 Continuing through March 20

We are also providing for those needing technology to support the alternative approach to learning that will take place in the upcoming weeks.

Beginning tomorrow, March 18, and continuing through Friday, March 20, parents/guardians who requested student technology (Chromebooks) will be able to pick them up at the Transportation Building, which is located by the parking lot on the Applebee’s side of the high school.

post_text:
Dear Parents, Community, and Staff

The Onondaga County Superintendents met with County Executive Ryan McMahon and County Health Commissioner Dr. Gupta earlier today to discuss COVID-19 and the potential impact on schools.

By now, you are likely all aware of the County Executive’s announcement in a 5:00 p.m. press conference of a State of Emergency in Onondaga County.

As per the order of the County Executive, students will be out of school beginning Monday, March 23, 2020. Students are scheduled to return on Tuesday, April 14.

The District plans to share more information tomorrow regarding this announcement. As we prepare for continuity of instruction for all of our students we anticipate using next week to solidify plans to meet the needs of our students.

We recognize that some of you may be uncomfortable sending your children to school. Please know that we respect your right as parents to choose what is best for your child.

Thank you,
David C. Bills
West Genesee CSD
Superintendent of Schools

https://www.westgenesee.org/message-supt-state-emerg/

Mark your Calendar for the West Genesee 12th Annual Culture Fair

The 12th annual Culture Fair will be held at West Genesee High School on Saturday, February 29 from 12:00-3:00 p.m in the upper gymnasium.

Join us as we celebrate our community’s diversity at this fun event featuring dance performances, live music, cultural demonstrations, food samples, artwork, T-shirts, kids crafts, and more!

The committee is looking for community members and organizations to participate with music performances, dancing, hosting a cultural booth, and/or sharing ethnic dish samples.

If you are interested in showcasing your culture, being a sponsor, or volunteering to work the event, please contact Rob Manipole at (315) 487-4673 or rmanipole@westgenesee.org.

This event is sponsored by the West Genesee PTA/PTO District Council, Camillus PBA, WGHS Student Council, and Tops Friendly Markets.

https://www.westgenesee.org/mark-your-calendar-for-the-west-genesee-12th-annual-culture-fair/

Food Pantry Information for Over the Break

Many students enjoy breakfast and lunch in our cafeterias on a regular basis. It is understandable when families find it challenging to provide those meals during school vacations.

Food pantries partner with the Food Bank of CNY to provide low cost, nutritious food to those in need. The following is a list of food pantries and services available in our community to assist families. Please know that you will be serviced by the food pantry nearest your legal address. If you have questions or need assistance please call: The Interreligious Food Consortium (IRC) weekdays at 315-474-8855 between the hours of 9:00 a.m. and 3:00 p.m. Their website is: http://www.ifccny.org/.

For more information listing the local food pantries, click here: https://www.westgenesee.org/food-pantry-information-for-over-the-break/

Congratulations to WGMS students Harrison Card (Grade 6) and Joseph Paoli (Grade 8 ), along with CMS student Payton Voss (Grade 8 ) for advancing Saturday to the oral round of The Post-Standard | syracuse.com | WCNY Spelling Bee.

They along with 32 other CNY students scored the highest among the 160 students who participated in the written qualifying exam at Christian Brothers Academy in DeWitt.

They oral round will be held at WCNY in Syracuse on Feb 29. The winner of the oral round will win a trip to Washington, D.C., to compete in the Scripps National Spelling Bee, which will be held May 24 to 29.
